cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new algorithm for inference and learning in Markov random fields (MRFs) using two variational distributions parameterized as neural networks. The paper focuses on machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper applies the proposed algorithm to various undirected generative models, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories.
